title: Rancho Cucamonga’s Bria Beale voted SoCal Prep Legends girls athlete of the week
text:
SoCal Prep Legends girls athlete of the week
Name: Bria Beale
School : Rancho Cucamonga
Sport: Girls volleyball
Year: Junior
Winning Numbers : Rancho Cucamonga junior Bria Beale was voted the SoCal Prep Legends girls athlete of the week with 9,543 votes when the polls closed Friday , barely finishing ahead of Saugus’ cross country standout Sydney Suarez, who finished with 8,540 votes.
In two matches last week , the 5-foot-11 outside-hitting Beale managed 18 kills to led Rancho to a victory over defending Baseline League champion Chino Hills, and registered 16 kills in a 3-0 win over Los Osos.
The Cougars also went 4-2 over the weekend in the prestigious Torrey Pines tournament with wins over elite foes in Marymount and Mira Costa. In that event, Beale tallied 43 kills and 41 digs, giving her 77 kills and 59 digs on the week.
Suarez led a strong Saugus showing at the Santa Clarita Valley Invitational last weekend at Lake Castaic Park, covering the three-mile course in 18 minutes, 11 seconds for a third-place finish and the top California mark. Her performance helped Saugus nail down the team title despite missing two regular runners.
Final Tally
LA Daily News: Sydney Suarez, Saugus, 8,540 Votes (46.7%)
Long Beach Press Telegram: Milan Stokes, LB Wilson, 53 Votes (0.3%)
SGVN: Katherine Muzi, Walnut, 17 Votes (0.1%)
Daily Bulletin: Bria Beale, Rancho Cucamonga, 9,543 Votes (52.2%)
Daily Breeze: Andrea Lee, Mira Costa, 41 Votes (0.2%)
Redlands Daily Facts/SB SUN: Katie Smith, Redlands, 80 Votes (0.4%)
WHAT IS SOCAL PREP LEGENDS : The best athletes in Southern California will be honored at an end-of-the-school-year awards show. For more details visit socalpreplegends.com , where you can also vote for the SoCal Athletes of the Week, as well as Play of the Week.
